snippet: Though the United States industrial economy has returned to 2006 levels, car sales — a sensitive economic indicator — have not. In Europe, sales continue to fall.
abstract: Floyd Norris Off The Charts column says auto sales, sensitive economic indicator, are not returning to pre-2006 levels as quickly as rest of United States industrial economy.
lead_paragraph: Though the United States industrial economy has returned to 2006 levels, car sales — a sensitive economic indicator — have not. In Europe, sales continue to fall.

headline.print_headline: Car Sales Worldwide Are Slow To Rebound
headline.seo: Car Sales Continue to Fall in Many Developed Countries
headline.main: Car Sales Worldwide Are Slow to Rebound
